how do i get through a baby with reflux when i have no family or friends here to help me and my husband works my husband works all day and he's tired when he gets home and i have no one else in the area that can help me please go back to your doctor insist that he she do something you may have to live with the spitting up but you can make it less painful for your baby if zantac doesn't work they can try prevacid or a number of other medications used to treat reflux insist on a referral to a pediatric gastroenterologist formula changes might or might not help including some prescription ones let your baby sleep in a swing bouncy chair car seat anything that keeps the baby upright my son is now and we went through this for months and months when he was a baby use receiving blankets as burp cloths lay back in a recliner chair with baby on your chest to snooze a bit some people swear by dr brown's bottles don't bother with a crib use things that keep the baby upright all of the time not just for half an hour after feeding my son could projectile vomit feet away hours after his last bottle i used a baby bjorn carrier and a sling to carry him all the time and that also meant i could have my hands free like someone else said find a mothers group cafemom com has some listed or people you might be able to connect to check your local bulletin boards for other moms who want to get together if you are desperate make sure your baby is safely buckled into something swing bouncy or whatever and lock yourself in the bathroom with the fan on and take a long hot shower turn a radio on for the baby or the television so the baby hears something and have yourself a good long cry and try to remember their are other people out there yahoo groups has a reflux group so does ivillage they are a huge source of information remember also that generally kids grow out of this between six months and a year oh if you are nursing you may try an elimination diet to avoid some of the most common allergens to babies as far as your husband try to have him care for the baby for half an hour each evening and leave the house go to the gym take a walk sit outside and talk on the phone with your mom or best friend just go i know it will be hard to convince him of it but just do it hand him the baby after he has been home for a while and just go outside don't ask just do it you can contact me via e mail if you have any questions i would be more than happy to talk to you Breastfeeding Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Humphrey Bogart Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Social rule Jam (TV series) The Shining (film) Medical prescription Little Britain Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Bart chalkboard gags Childbirth Medicine Knots Landing Milton H. Erickson Shaggy dog story The Inside Pet skunk Sin City Piccolo Junior Saga The Adventures of Pete & Pete The Amber Spyglass Blood Simple Ben Johnson (athlete) Aerial (dance move) Fecal incontinence Mattress The Family from One End Street Prostate cancer Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe EastEnders Pok__mon Live! The Marshall Mathers LP Coeliac disease Theory of conduct Jon Secada Kodocha What Ever Happened to Baby Jane? (film) Pope John Paul I The Curse of Fenric Friends Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina Casualty lifting Time Out of Mind The Ashlee Simpson Show Hormone replacement therapy (trans) First aid Phoebe Buffay's songs Terri Schiavo 2005 trial of Michael Jackson History of As the World Turns (2000-present) Rose (Doctor Who) Hamster Swingout RuneScape quests Jackass: The Movie Infant Characters in the Smurfs Damn Yankees Avenue Q Kender Eddie Guerrero Characters of Lost Hey Jude Phil Hendrie Laura Schlessinger Care Bears Good Morning, Vietnam Migraine Sleeping Murder Rent (musical) Bringing It All Back Home Comanche Apollo 8 Situation comedy Neighbours Futurama (TV series - season 4) Toilet humour Melanie Wilkes Ocean's Twelve Baby transport Days of our Lives Eternal Sunshi